Colspan attribute : when we use this,we can get a header that spans over 2 or more columns
 The value of the colspan attribute represents the number of columns to span.
Rowspan attribute: To make a cell span over multiple rows, use the rowspan attribute
The value of the rowspan attribute represents the number of rows to span.
Padding: Cell padding is the space between the cell edges and cell content
To add padding on table cells, use css padding property
To add the padding only above the content, use the padding-top property
To change the space between table cells, use the CSS border-spacing property
Colgroup element is used to style specific columns of a table
You can hide columns with the visibility: collapse property.

div element is often used as a container for other HTML elements.
div element has no required attributes but style,class and id are common.
